WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:01.384
Alright!

00:00:01.384 --> 00:00:04.068
Let's set up SSH keys so you

00:00:04.068 --> 00:00:06.369
can reach your servers without passwords.

00:00:06.369 --> 00:00:07.903
This is pure SSH;

00:00:07.903 --> 00:00:09.438
rdc isn't involved yet.

00:00:10.205 --> 00:00:11.200
Two ideas.

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:14.186
Generate one key on your laptop,

00:00:14.186 --> 00:00:17.171
then authorize it on each server

00:00:17.171 --> 00:00:18.166
with ssh-copy-id.

00:00:18.166 --> 00:00:19.161
Generate once,

00:00:19.161 --> 00:00:20.654
copy per server.

00:00:23.907 --> 00:00:24.352
First,

00:00:24.352 --> 00:00:27.025
generate a new SSH key on

00:00:27.025 --> 00:00:27.916
your laptop.

00:00:27.916 --> 00:00:29.252
Ed25519 is secure,

00:00:29.252 --> 00:00:29.698
small,

00:00:29.698 --> 00:00:31.034
and well supported.

00:00:31.034 --> 00:00:32.816
You do this once;

00:00:32.816 --> 00:00:35.489
the same key works for every

00:00:35.489 --> 00:00:36.825
server you add.

00:00:36.825 --> 00:00:38.607
This is plain SSH,

00:00:38.607 --> 00:00:40.834
independent of any tooling here.

00:00:41.634 --> 00:00:42.253
Key generated.

00:00:42.253 --> 00:00:45.035
The public half is what we copy to each

00:00:45.035 --> 00:00:45.344
server.

00:00:48.655 --> 00:00:51.553
Now authorize the key on your first

00:00:51.553 --> 00:00:52.794
server with ssh-copy-id.

00:00:52.794 --> 00:00:55.692
It appends your public key to the

00:00:55.692 --> 00:00:56.934
server's authorized list,

00:00:56.934 --> 00:00:59.417
so future logins skip the password.

00:01:01.417 --> 00:01:03.194
Authorized on the first server.

00:01:03.194 --> 00:01:04.970
No more password prompts there.

00:01:08.307 --> 00:01:11.198
Do the same for every other server

00:01:11.198 --> 00:01:12.024
you manage.

00:01:12.024 --> 00:01:14.502
Here we authorize the second one.

00:01:14.502 --> 00:01:16.980
Just repeat ssh-copy-id for each machine.

00:01:18.980 --> 00:01:21.088
Both servers now trust this key.

00:01:21.088 --> 00:01:22.846
SSH is fully set up.

00:01:23.684 --> 00:01:26.315
Your key is set and your servers

00:01:26.315 --> 00:01:27.067
trust it.

00:01:27.067 --> 00:01:27.819
Next up,

00:01:27.819 --> 00:01:30.450
we add your first server to rdc.
